title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 §§ 765-1.5 - Withdrawals of applications
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 §§ 765-1.5 - Withdrawals of applications

State Regulations

An application made to the Public Health Council may, on written request of the applicant, be withdrawn prior to decision by the
council at any time without prejudice to resubmission. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10
§§
765-1.5

State regulations are updated quarterly; we currently have two versions available. Below is a
comparison between our most recent version and the prior quarterly release. More comparison features will be added as we have more versions to compare. No prior version found.
